//4- print a triangular pattern of *
//Ans-
/*Algorithm-
step1- Start:
Initialize variables pe, avg, m, and sum=0.
step2- Read Values:
Start a loop from i=1 to i=5:
Read the value of m for each iteration.
step3- Calculate Sum:
Start a loop from i=1 to i=5:
Add the value of m to sum (i.e., sum += m).
step4- Calculate Percentage and Average:
Calculate pe as (sum/500)*100.
step5- Calculate avg as sum/5.
step6- Display Results:
Display the values of pe and avg.
step7- Stop:
End the program. */

//code
#include<stdio.h>
#include<stdlib.h>
int main(){
int i, space, rows=6, k = 0;
for(i=1;i<=rows;i++,k=0){
    for(space=1;space<=rows-i;space++){
        printf(" ");
    }
    while(k!=2*i-1){
        printf("*");
        k++;
    }
    printf("\n");
}
}
